{"TopicId":25982,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Drag Question","CreatedByName":"hansman1982","CreatedById":62705,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-08T03:23:01Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"hansman1982","CreatedById":62705,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-08T03:23:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EDo parts that are under other parts still contribute to drag? Say I use a nosecone with 0 drag but the SRB underneath has 1 drag. Does it still count as 1 drag or 0 drag?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-08T03:24:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EYes, the game\u0027s aerodynamic system is a placeholder, and all parts contribute to drag, even when they\u0027re not exposed to airflow. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"hansman1982","CreatedById":62705,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-08T03:30:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EOh, are there mods that give nosecones negative drag then? Otherwise, I see no point besides looks.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"maackey","CreatedById":39248,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-08T03:33:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://kerbalspaceprogram.com/ferram-aerospace-research/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://kerbalspaceprogram.com/ferram-aerospace-research/\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDoes much better than giving nosecones negative drag \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"UmbralRaptor","CreatedById":2767,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-08T03:34:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022hansman1982\u0022 data-cite=\u0022hansman1982\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EOh, are there mods that give nosecones negative drag then? Otherwise, I see no point besides looks.\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESomewhat. There\u0027s \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/showthread.php/20451-0-19-Ferram-Aerospace-Research-v0-9-2-Aerodynamics-Fixes-For-Planes-Rockets\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/a\u003E, which completely overhauls the aerodynamic model.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"hansman1982","CreatedById":62705,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-08T03:58:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EAwesome! Thank you everyone!\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"hansman1982","CreatedById":62705,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-08T04:00:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ENow, to find a mod that gets Kerbal to use all of my processors so I can actually play the game without ridiculous lag.\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}